The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Sunday, April 25, 2004 				 SC trouble for Dharam 
																								New Delhi, April 24: The controversy surrounding Dharmendras marriage to Hema Malini has reached the Supreme Court, reports our legal correspondent. 																								Advocate D.K. Garg has sought disqualification of Dharmendra from contesting elections for non-disclosure and false declaration of affidavit along with his nomination papers. 																								Dharmendra is contesting for the Bikaner Lok Sabha seat as a BJP candidate. Hema is a star campaigner for the party.																								The Indore district and sessions court today reserved order for Monday  when Bikaner votes  on a complaint against Dharmendra, who allegedly embraced Islam in 1969 to marry Hema without divorcing his first wife under the Hindu law. 																								The advocate argued that Dharmendra has disclosed possessing wealth to the tune of Rs 13 crore with his wife, but has not disclosed (the) name of his wife.
